name: places/ChIJP8GJet4Z2jERhiwYobK0284/reviews/ChZDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnTURvaWZ2aFFBEAE
text:
{'text': 'Quite long queue as cafe was busy, we waited for about 20 mins. Nice atmosphere with nice music. Tried their Osmanthus Oolong Cake, Tiramisu Cream Latte and Hot Cappuccino.
Osmanthus Oolong cake was quite nice and fluffy, the sponge cake inside was light, moist and soft, but the cream was a bit too sweet for my liking. Coffee was good and smooth, balanced well with the milk. Tiramisu Cream Latte was creamy and good too.
Tried also their Roasted Genmaicha Gelato. The tea taste was strong and bittersweet. It‚Äôs sweet at first then got a bitter tea aftertaste.
Overall was good experience. Service was quite slow though, but staff were helpful.
Next visit: Tried their Dirty Matcha and Matcha Strawberry Teacake for our tea time. Dirty Matcha was good, creamy and strong matcha flavour, balanced with the coffee taste. The teacake was nice, moist and wonderful, not too sweet. Both drink and teacake was enjoyable.', 'languageCode': 'en'}

name: places/ChIJP8GJet4Z2jERhiwYobK0284/reviews/ChZDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnTURJLWJURWJnEAE
text: {'text': "Ordered the all day brunch and it was served hot. The flavor wise is on point and flavorful, from the egg, to the mushrooms, to the German sausage. Also got the black sesame latte and it was rich and thick but not overpowering like black sesame paste. It's unsweetened just the way I like it. The ambience here is abit noisy on a Friday night as everyone is just happily chatting away. During the time I'm here the seats were constantly occupied. The staff was also very friendly and polite. Would come back again.", 'languageCode': 'en'}
